column657: Cav-2::Cre virus injections were performed on mice aged P30-P33. To limit the spread of viral particles allowing for layer- or pathway-specific injections, iontophoresis was used for all injections at 5 mA, 7 s on/3 s off, for a total of 10 min. The following stereotaxic coordinates were used: deep layer S1 (AP: 1, ML: 3, DV: 0.85). Ten days following injection, mice were euthanized and perfused for analysis.
column658: Cav-2::Cre virus injections were performed on mice aged P30-P33. To limit the spread of viral particles allowing for layer- or pathway-specific injections, iontophoresis was used for all injections at 5 mA, 7 s on/3 s off, for a total of 10 min. The following stereotaxic coordinates were used: superficial layer S1 (AP: 1, ML: 3, DV: 0.15, 25 degrees tilt). Ten days following injection, mice were euthanized and perfused for analysis.

column684: Images of the full RGC dendritic field morphology were acquired with 20x magnification at a x/y/z resolution of 0.15 x 0.15 x 0.31 microns, while images of the soma, as well as proximal axon with AIS labeling were acquired with a 63x oil immersion objective (NA=1.4) at a x/y/z resolution of 0.09 x 0.09 X 0.31 microns. A straight axon was purposefully added by the original authors to the traced cells to avoid the edge effects at axon terminals when simulating extracellular electric stimulation and its impact on RGCs

column738: To achieve sparse labeling of a few dozens of cortical neurons, a mixture of AAV2/1-hSyn-Cre and AAV2/1-CAG-Flex-EGFP was injected. The viral mixture was delivered through an oil hydraulic micromanipulator (Narishige, MO-10, 17 nL/min for 50 nL) into ALM (AP: +2.5, ML: 1.5, DV: 0.7). Each mouse was injected unilaterally and maintained for 5 weeks to allow stable and strong expression of EGFP.

column1738: Recombinant human caspase-6 C163A was activated in Stennicke buffer at 37 Celsius degrees for 15 min and diluted to 10 pg/10 microL in internal solution with 30-60 micromolar Alexa 594 or 40-80 micromolar Alexa 488, and osmolarity double checked to be around 310 mOsm. These reconstructions were done from 2-photon laser-scanning microscopy image stacks, which means compartment diameters may appear larger than they are. These reconstructions may therefore not be suitable for multicompartmental computer simulations (Blackman et al., Frontiers in Synaptic Neuroscience 2013, DOI: 10.3389/fnsyn.2013.00011).

column1827: Large big-tufted cells with the apical dendrite often bifurcating close to the soma, suggesting that these were corticospinal cells. They had bigger hyperpolarization sag, lower input resistance, and smaller AP width, compared to the L5 IT neurons. We did not observe consistent morpho-electric differences between the four ET types, apart from L5 ET_1 being located deeper than the rest, but they may have different projection targets.
